## ✍️ Brand Voice & Tone
We speak **Engineer-to-Engineer**. We are direct, urgent, and evidence-based.

- **Direct**: "Your AI Agent Will Go Rogue. SupraWall Makes Sure It Can't." (Not "AI agents might have issues").
- **Deterministic**: We use words like *Intercept*, *Enforce*, *Sovereignty*, *Evidence*, *Signed*.
- **Problem-First**: Always lead with the threat (Prompt Injection, 404 Hubs, Rogue Transfers), then provide the one-line fix.
- **No Fluff**: We avoid marketing-speak. If we can't show it in 10 lines of Python or a deterministic audit log, it doesn't exist.

---

## ⌨️ Typography
- **Headlines**: Semi-condensed, font-black (900), tracking-tighter. Italicized for emphasis.
- **Subheadlines**: All-caps, tracking-widest, bold. Used for Tag Badges.
- **Body**: High-readability sans-serif (Inter/Geist). Italicized for secondary "technical insights."
- **Code**: Monospace (Fira Code/JetBrains Mono). Always syntax-highlighted.

